â€œVery peaceful name for a very relaxing strain. Scooped up some small bud for a good price. These buds were a light green with dark brown pistols, light purple and magenta hues, dark green calyxes. The trichomes sparkle really brightly against the purples. Hibiscus Sunrise has a flowery sweet scent with a hint of lavender. When vaped the tongue is greeted with flowery sweetness. Hibiscus Sunrise was recommended by the...â€

â€œNot my favorite. I don't find it clear headed, I find it rather foggy. Foggy and loud (stimulus = more overwhelming) with some euphoria. Granted, the euphoria is nice, but there are just other strains out there I prefer to smoke with less negatives. It's not terrible its just nothing special. Kush Rise (Hibiscus Sunrise x Rugburn OG) on the other hand is one of my new favorites by Colorado Seed Inc.â€

â€œGot a great deal on a 29% thc outdoor o.z. Gambled on the strain. Turns out.... Not bad at all. A light orange citrus taste with a soft mango smell in the jar. Nice cerebral relaxing buzz. Way more potent and awesome than I expected on bargain outdoor. $120 in Trinidad COâ€
